Description: Companion package for the book: "Robust Statistics: Theory and Methods, 2nd edition", <http://www.wiley.com/go/maronna/robust>.  This package contains code that implement the robust estimators discussed in the recent second edition of the book above, as well as the scripts reproducing the examples in it. 
Depends: R (>= 3.0.2), fit.models
Imports: stats, graphics, utils, methods, DEoptimR, pyinit, rrcov, robustbase, shiny, shinyjs, PerformanceAnalytics, DT, ggplot2, gridExtra, robust, xts
Suggests: knitr
